1. Medical Imaging & Diagnosis
• AI used in X-rays, MRIs, CT scans
• Detects tumors, fractures, pneumonia, etc.
• Helps radiologists → faster + fewer missed cases
• Example tasks:
• Cancer detection
• Stroke identification
2. Predictive Analytics (Patient Risk)
• Uses patient history + vitals
• Predicts:
• Hospital readmission
• Disease progression
• ICU risk
• Helps doctors intervene earlier
3. Remote Patient Monitoring
• Wearables + sensors track:
• Heart rate
• Blood glucose
• Oxygen levels
• AI flags abnormal patterns
• Reduces hospital visits & costs
4. Electronic Health Records (EHR) Automation
• AI summarizes patient notes
• Auto-fills documentation
• Reduces doctor burnout
• Improves data accuracy
5. Drug Discovery & Development (added use case)
• AI simulates drug interactions
• Speeds up testing phases
• Reduces R&D costs
• Especially useful for rare diseases
6. Personalized Treatment Plans (added use case)
• Tailors treatments using:
• Genetics
• Lifestyle data
• Medical history
• More effective than one-size-fits-all care
Agriculture — AI Use Cases
1. Precision Farming
• AI analyzes soil, weather, crop data
• Optimizes:
• Planting schedules
• Fertilizer use
• Water usage
• Leads to higher yields, less waste
2. Crop Disease & Pest Detection
• Computer vision via:
• Drones
• Cameras
• Identifies diseases early
• Prevents large-scale crop loss
3. Smart Irrigation Systems
• AI decides when and how much to water
• Uses:
• Soil moisture
• Weather forecasts
• Saves water + energy
4. Autonomous Machinery
• Self-driving tractors & harvesters
• Perform:
• Plowing
• Seeding
• Harvesting
• Reduces labor costs
5. Yield Prediction (added use case)
• AI forecasts crop output before harvest
• Helps farmers:
• Plan storage
• Set pricing
• Reduce financial risk
6. Supply Chain Optimization (added use case)
• Predicts demand & spoilage
• Optimizes transport routes
• Reduces food waste
• Improves market efficiency
Key Takeaways
• Healthcare AI → improves diagnosis, efficiency, and patient outcomes
• Agriculture AI → boosts productivity, sustainability, and food security
• Both rely heavily on:
• Machine Learning
• Computer Vision
• Sensor & IoT data
